Just starts with your diet. Focus on vegetables, salad, and protein (egg whites, yogurt, etc.), opt for fish or white meat over red meats, eat more frequently throughout the day so that you don't overeat at meal times, and drink lots of water! As for exercises, start with 40 minutes to an hour of cardio. You don't need to go run a marathon, but try fast-walking, the elliptical, or jogging for a few minutes at a time.

LeilaniHapa I second that about diet. Eat clean, wholesome foods, cut the processed junk, and exercise regularly. Also, drink LOTS of water, you’d be surprised how much it contributes to weight loss. You can do it, just believe in yourself, stick to your regimen, and know that it takes time. There is no quick fix, so the only way you’ll hit your goal weight is by working hard and staying true to yourself. Start with your cardio, this gets your body into the fat-burning range, and work on bodyweight exercises from there. There are also a ton of calisthenics-based fitness gurus on YouTube that will really be able to help you out, I recommend this if you’re trying to go for an “angel physique”.
